04:48.322 --> 04:51.790
Mr. Byrne: Wha-- your stage?!
This is my gym!

04:51.859 --> 04:53.959
This is st. Brigid's.

04:53.961 --> 04:56.761
Ball hockey is a religion!
- Ugh!

04:56.797 --> 04:59.531
- And my b'ys need practice
just as much as your girls -

04:59.533 --> 05:02.300
And mark and ritchie.
[shrill whistle blast]

05:02.303 --> 05:05.403
- What part are you trying for?
Hamar? Casca?

05:05.538 --> 05:08.807
- Stage manager!
Or maybe props master.

05:08.809 --> 05:11.743
Is it better to be a manager
or a master?

05:13.680 --> 05:15.514
- It's better to be a star!

05:15.649 --> 05:17.915
You could try for casca
the centurion?

05:17.951 --> 05:19.751
It's only one line,
but you'd be onstage

05:19.820 --> 05:21.853
For almost the whole show.

05:21.855 --> 05:23.788
- Nah, you're the actor.

05:23.824 --> 05:25.490
I bet you get the lead;

05:25.492 --> 05:28.025
You can really work a crowd.
- I'm sure there's plenty

05:28.062 --> 05:29.828
Of kids who'll give me a run
for my money...

05:29.830 --> 05:32.297
[shrill whistle blast]
but thank you.

05:32.299 --> 05:34.265
[ruler thwaps loudly]

05:34.335 --> 05:36.634
- Tina, why don't you
start us off?

05:37.905 --> 05:39.938
<i> [shrill whistle blast,</i>
<i> indistinct chatter]</i>

05:44.044 --> 05:45.844
- [quietly] "sorry, centurion.

05:45.913 --> 05:47.445
There are no... Free refills."

05:47.514 --> 05:49.214
<i> [shrill whistle blast]</i>

05:49.216 --> 05:50.648
<i> Adult mark: Oh, tina.</i>

05:50.718 --> 05:53.251
<i> I guess her dad never told her</i>
<i> about the deaf old man.</i>

05:53.253 --> 05:54.920
<i> [shrill whistle blast]</i>

05:56.023 --> 05:57.789
<i> This was a lock.</i>

05:59.626 --> 06:02.661
- Oh! Anything for me?
- Uh... Let me check.

06:02.663 --> 06:04.529
Bills...
[mail rustles]

06:04.531 --> 06:07.465
Magazine for mom.
- Mm-hmm.

06:07.467 --> 06:10.334
- And cpp for you and--
- what?!

06:10.471 --> 06:11.836
- Elizabeth critch.
- Give me that!

06:11.905 --> 06:13.472
- Grandma?
- What do you read my mail for?

06:13.607 --> 06:16.007
That's a federal offense!
- You asked me to.

06:16.009 --> 06:18.543
- Aye, well, why aren't you
at school?

06:18.545 --> 06:20.779
Ah, you-- go on with ya

06:20.781 --> 06:22.881
Before I rat you out
for being on the pip.

06:23.951 --> 06:25.683
- You're welcome.

06:26.720 --> 06:28.620
- What are you goin' on about?

06:28.755 --> 06:29.421
- Nothing!

06:31.258 --> 06:32.891
[marching band music plays]

06:32.960 --> 06:35.160
- What fresh hell is this?

06:35.295 --> 06:38.163
♪♪♪

06:38.298 --> 06:39.664
<i> [shrill whistle blast]</i>

06:39.666 --> 06:41.566
Lovely, dear.

06:41.568 --> 06:43.502
[shoes squeak,
players grunt and yell]

06:43.637 --> 06:46.404
Who's next? Mark.

06:46.407 --> 06:48.539
[piano intro plays]

06:49.910 --> 06:51.843
[players shout, sticks thwap]

06:53.580 --> 06:56.514
- Centurion! I recognize
the man you describe!

06:56.583 --> 06:58.717
He's upstairs with a dozen
of his friends.

06:58.719 --> 07:00.185
Cheap bunch.

07:00.254 --> 07:02.520
They ordered one fish, a loaf,
and a jug of water,

07:02.589 --> 07:04.589
And want thirteen different
bills.

07:04.591 --> 07:07.124
Go on in!
Get those bums out of here!

07:07.161 --> 07:08.927
Adult mark: And the oscar
goes to...

07:08.929 --> 07:10.394
- It's nice, mark.

07:10.431 --> 07:12.164
<i> Adult mark: Nice?!</i>
<i> I killed it!</i>

07:12.299 --> 07:13.999
<i>She was probably downplaying it</i>

07:14.001 --> 07:16.835
<i>So the other kids wouldn't feel</i>
<i> totally inferior.</i>

07:16.837 --> 07:18.770
[hard whack, ball thuds]
- ow!

07:18.839 --> 07:20.505
[everyone laughs]

07:20.640 --> 07:23.842
- That's it! I warned you.
- Ow!

07:23.911 --> 07:26.111
- Your ball is mine now, byrne!

07:26.113 --> 07:27.812
- Hey, I need that to finish
the game!

07:27.815 --> 07:29.881
- And I need more kids
for this play.

07:29.883 --> 07:32.217
Whoever shot this ball
is in the play

07:32.352 --> 07:34.653
Or you're not getting your ball
back, sir.

07:34.788 --> 07:37.255
- Yeah, sure, sounds fair.

07:37.390 --> 07:40.091
Go on, fox.
- No way! I'm the best player!

07:40.226 --> 07:41.626
- Now!

07:41.695 --> 07:45.263
[stick clatters]
- you're dead for this, critch.

07:45.265 --> 07:46.764
- You're the one who hit me!

07:46.834 --> 07:48.967
- Come on, up you go.

07:48.969 --> 07:50.468
[players chuckle]

07:50.504 --> 07:52.237
[script rustles]
- move!

07:52.306 --> 07:54.206
[indistinct chatter]

07:57.644 --> 07:58.610
[dramatic music plays]

07:58.745 --> 08:00.345
<i> - [readying exhale]</i>

08:00.480 --> 08:02.113
[angrily] they're just
poor men!

08:02.149 --> 08:03.781
