to serve them?

08:03.817 --> 08:05.583
When do I get a break?!

08:05.652 --> 08:07.451
Someone should serve me!

08:07.488 --> 08:09.153
[dramatic music swells,
then fades]

08:09.189 --> 08:11.456
- [gasps] the intensity!

08:11.525 --> 08:12.790
Bravo!

08:12.826 --> 08:14.459
[hands clap lightly]

08:14.528 --> 08:17.229
<i> [stunned laugh]</i>

08:17.364 --> 08:18.696
- She's amazing.

08:18.698 --> 08:20.398
- It was a little big.

08:20.400 --> 08:22.366
- What about you, ritchie?

08:24.137 --> 08:26.871
- Oh, rit-ritchie's more
of a props guy.

08:26.874 --> 08:29.774
Heart of gold,
but he isn't an actor like me.

08:29.910 --> 08:32.110
- Oh, he isn't, is he?

08:32.179 --> 08:34.679
- He's just not cut out
for stage work.

08:34.748 --> 08:37.415
He's a behind-the-scenes guy.

08:37.417 --> 08:40.117
Heart and soul
of the operation.

08:40.153 --> 08:41.986
- I've made my decision.

08:42.022 --> 08:43.855
Fox will play the innkeeper's
wife

08:43.857 --> 08:46.657
And ritchie will be hamar,
the innkeeper.

08:47.694 --> 08:49.427
- Me?
- Him?!

08:49.496 --> 08:51.029
But he didn't even audition!

08:51.031 --> 08:52.697
- Well, maybe he would have

08:52.699 --> 08:54.832
If you had been more
supportive, mark.

08:54.834 --> 08:57.068
Or should I say,
casca the centurion.

08:57.203 --> 08:59.771
- Casca?! But...
He only has one line

09:00.908 --> 09:03.041
