I swear, I swear,

12:07.293 --> 12:09.494
I'll report you -

12:09.563 --> 12:11.195
I mean, her dead next week.

12:13.433 --> 12:15.566
You have my word on it.

12:17.337 --> 12:19.970
- Now, ritchie, I hope
you've memorized your lines.

12:20.006 --> 12:21.606
You're our little star.

12:21.741 --> 12:23.241
- Don't worry, sister.

12:23.376 --> 12:24.909
My dad's been helping me
learn them.

12:25.044 --> 12:27.612
- Oh, he must be very proud.

12:27.747 --> 12:29.914
<i>Adult mark: As ritchie's love</i>
<i> of the stage grew,</i>

12:30.049 --> 12:32.516
<i> Mine faded like</i>
<i> a broken spotlight.</i>

12:32.552 --> 12:34.852
Sister margaret: Action!

12:34.888 --> 12:37.155
- [woodenly] there you are,
dear wife!

12:37.224 --> 12:39.457
How goes it in the party room?

12:39.592 --> 12:41.593
- Not great, hamar.

12:41.595 --> 12:43.727
They're all sitting on
the same side of the table.

12:43.764 --> 12:47.364
- That table should seat
twenty-four!

12:47.400 --> 12:49.467
<i> We need the space,</i>

12:49.602 --> 12:52.136
It's thirsty Thursday!

12:52.205 --> 12:54.205
<i> Adult mark: Ritchie was so bad</i>

12:54.340 --> 12:55.873
<i> That even sister margaret</i>
<i> was having trouble</i>

12:55.909 --> 12:58.142
<i> Believing in the bible.</i>

12:58.145 --> 13:00.311
- So... What'd you think?

13:01.615 --> 13:03.581
- Uh... Very interesting
choices.

13:03.650 --> 13:05.750
I mean, I... I wouldn't make
them myself,

13:05.752 --> 13:07.885
But who cares what everyone
else thinks, right?

13:09.055 --> 13:11.055
- Was it that bad?

13:11.124 --> 13:12.990
[marker squeaks]

13:12.992 --> 13:15.026
Maybe you should
just do it then.

13:15.095 --> 13:17.094
<i> Adult mark: Time to steal</i>
<i> the spotlight!</i>

13:17.164 --> 13:19.564
- I guess. I mean, if you told
sister margaret

13:19.633 --> 13:22.033
You really, really
don't wanna be hamar,

13:22.102 --> 13:24.302
I... Could do it.

13:24.304 --> 13:26.638
You could still do props!

13:26.640 --> 13:28.239
It's a win-win.

13:28.275 --> 13:29.841
<i> Fox: Sister!</i>

13:29.976 --> 13:32.843
Mark's trying to get ritchie
to drop out and do props.

13:32.845 --> 13:35.045
- That's a lie!
Adult mark: That was the truth.

13:35.081 --> 13:37.248
- Since you seem to be having
trouble learning humility,

13:37.383 --> 13:39.884
I'll help you: You're out
of the play altogether.

13:40.019 --> 13:42.753
- Uh, I need to learn that
humility stuff.

13:42.823 --> 13:44.655
Kick me out, too, sister!

13:45.859 --> 13:48.593
- Please, I'll do anything!

13:48.728 --> 13:50.327
- Okay, you can do the job

13:50.363 --> 13:52.196
You're so anxious for ritchie
to do:

13:52.199 --> 13:53.931
Props.

13:55.135 --> 13:58.469
Now, ritchie,
let's take it from the...

13:58.538 --> 14:00.871
"no shoes, no service"
foot washing scene.

14:00.873 --> 14:02.907
- I like that scene.

14:04.143 --> 14:06.577
- And this time,
don't be afraid to act.

14:08.148 --> 14:10.949
- [woodenly] no shoes,
no service.

14:12.552 --> 14:13.952
<i>Sister margaret: Jesus, mary,</i>
<i> and joseph.</i>

14:15.588 --> 14:17.454
[car rumbles]
mike sr.: Come on, will ya?!

14:17.490 --> 14:18.990
The play starts in
half an hour!

14:19.125 --> 14:21.259
What's the hold up?!
- I waiting for a phone call,

14:21.328 --> 14:24.495
But... [sighs] I guess
we'd better go.

14:24.564 --> 14:26.631
- [yelling] mike,
get in the car!

14:28.167 --> 14:30.568
[phone rings]

14:30.570 --> 14:33.504
[running footsteps]

14:33.573 --> 14:35.106
- Name?
- Elizabeth critch.

14:35.241 --> 14:37.241
- Birthday?
- June 29th.

14:37.244 --> 14:39.077
- Really? I wasn't even
in the ballpark.

14:39.212 --> 14:42.146
- I don't think I can do this.
- Yes, you can!

14:42.148 --> 14:45.116
Nobody better at talking about
other people than you!

14:45.251 --> 14:47.985
You were born for this moment.
[phone continues ringing]

14:50.523 --> 14:52.657
[handset rattles]
- hello?

14:53.860 --> 14:57.061
[clears throat]
yes, this is elizabeth critch.

14:57.196 --> 14:59.396
Well, of course I'm alive!
Doesn't it sound like it?

14:59.432 --> 15:01.332
- Yes, yes!

15:01.467 --> 15:05.803
June 29th, 1908. I remember
like it was yesterday.

15:05.805 --> 15:07.204
[giggles lightly]

15:07.240 --> 15:09.407
Oh, don't go telling anyone
[gasps] my age

15:09.409 --> 15:11.675
Because I still get carded
at the liquor store

15:11.711 --> 15:14.746
When the light is right.
- [laughs quietly]

15:14.881 --> 15:17.348
- Oh! Oh, I'm feeling feverish.
- What?

15:18.551 --> 15:20.618
Oh, I'm having... [gasps]
trouble breathing.

15:20.620 --> 15:22.286
[gasps for breath]
oh, there's a light

15:22.355 --> 15:23.955
And a tunnel - daddy,
is that you?

15:24.090 --> 15:25.556
I am going to the light now,
bye!

15:25.625 --> 15:28.292
[handset clangs loudly]
- wha--

15:28.361 --> 15:31.495
- I guess that's it.
[phone rings]

15:31.531 --> 15:32.964
Hmm?
- Mm...

15:33.099 --> 15:35.833
[handset rattles]
hello? Yes.

15:35.869 --> 15:37.768
This is he.

15:37.804 --> 15:41.706
Oh, my wife, uh... Passed.

15:43.310 --> 15:46.711
So don't send anymore cheques...

15:46.780 --> 15:48.479
Unless... Elizabeth,
are you rallying?

15:48.481 --> 15:50.180
- [hard slap] just--
- no, no, no, um...

15:50.216 --> 15:52.249
Dead as a dodo.

15:52.285 --> 15:55.019
Yes, well, have a nice day.

15:58.157 --> 16:00.257
[handset clicks]

16:00.293 --> 16:02.193
Why bother going
to the theatre?

16:02.328 --> 16:04.395
- [laughs]
- I... I mean that was...

16:04.431 --> 16:08.065
The best acting I ever saw
in this town

16:08.101 --> 16:10.067
Was that tonight.
- [laughs]

16:10.203 --> 16:11.735
- That was brilliant.

16:11.771 --> 16:13.671
<i> [laughs goofily,</i>
<i> horn blasts outside]</i>

16:13.673 --> 16:15.706
Off you go.

16:15.742 --> 16:17.675
- Aww, aren't you coming?

16:17.677 --> 16:19.276
- No. No,

16:20.780 --> 16:23.648
I have someone I need to see.

16:24.751 --> 16:27.317
Mm. [chuckles softly,
then sighs]

16:29.122 --> 16:30.721
<i> [door bangs shut]</i>

16:30.790 --> 16:33.424
♪♪♪

16:33.559 --> 16:35.092
<i> Adult mark: Opening night.</i>

16:35.128 --> 16:36.927
<i> In mere moments,</i>
<i> the curtain would go up</i>

16:36.963 --> 16:38.696
<i> And the spotlight would hit</i>
<i> the stage,</i>

16:38.698 --> 16:41.165
<i> Illuminating my lies</i>
<i> to the world.</i>

16:41.167 --> 16:43.434
<i> I had no idea what</i>
<i> my end game was.</i>

16:44.637 --> 16:46.370
Mary: Love your dress.
Oh, 'scuse me, 'scuse me.

16:46.373 --> 16:48.305
Mike sr.: Made it.
It's a big night!

16:48.341 --> 16:50.274
- Yes, yes. You know,
it's not everyday

16:50.276 --> 16:52.443
That your son is the star.
- [chuckles]

16:52.578 --> 16:54.511
Thank you.

16:55.581 --> 16:57.715
[indistinct chatter]

16:57.850 --> 16:59.116
[camera whirs]

17:02.288 --> 17:04.588
- I know you must be nervous.
- No.

17:04.624 --> 17:05.956
- I know you're probably
terrified

17:05.992 --> 17:07.091
You'll forget a line.

17:07.226 --> 17:09.227
- Nope. I know 'em all.

17:09.362 --> 17:12.196
- I can't imagine what's going
on inside your stomach.

17:12.198 --> 17:14.298
- I'm getting pizza after.

17:14.300 --> 17:16.734
<i> Adult mark: It was useless.</i>
<i> He was unflappable.</i>

17:16.869 --> 17:18.536
<i> And as much as I wanted</i>
<i> the part,</i>

17:18.671 --> 17:21.806
<i> I wanted ritchie to be happy</i>
<i> even more.</i>

17:21.875 --> 17:24.475
- I just wanted to say
I'm sorry.

17:24.511 --> 17:26.610
And I know you'll be
the best hamar ever.

17:26.679 --> 17:29.347
- Thanks.
- You're gonna be great.

17:29.349 --> 17:31.014
Just had a look.

17:31.051 --> 17:33.751
There's a load of people
out there.

17:33.886 --> 17:35.119
[sighs heavily]

17:35.254 --> 17:37.755
I guess...
I'll go back to props.

17:39.025 --> 17:41.426
[camera beeps and whirs,
indistinct chatter]

17:41.561 --> 17:43.494
<i> Adult mark: Ritchie had gotten</i>
<i> over his stage fright</i>

17:43.530 --> 17:45.529
<i> And discovered his audience</i>
<i> fright.</i>

17:45.598 --> 17:47.331
[stomach rumbles loudly]

17:47.467 --> 17:49.366
[low, indistinct murmurs]

17:49.402 --> 17:51.168
[middle eastern music plays]

17:51.204 --> 17:54.105
[audience applauds
and whistles]

17:56.709 --> 17:58.642
- Welcome. Table for one?

17:58.678 --> 18:01.412
Gary: Party of thirteen!
Judas is the name.

18:01.414 --> 18:03.614
There's more where
this came from.

18:03.616 --> 18:06.384
[coin clatters]

18:06.386 --> 18:08.719
[audience titters and murmurs]

18:09.856 --> 18:11.122
<i> Adult mark: I had been jealous</i>
<i> of ritchie</i>

18:11.257 --> 18:13.925
<i> But, in that moment,</i>
<i> I sure did not wanna be him.</i>

18:14.060 --> 18:15.860
[tense music plays]

18:21.301 --> 18:23.134
<i> Adult mark: I had been dying</i>
<i> to play hamar,</i>

18:23.269 --> 18:25.903
<i>But ritchie was dying on stage.</i>

18:25.972 --> 18:28.172
Fox: I said,
where shall we seat him?

18:29.242 --> 18:31.342
<i> Audience: [indistinct murmurs]</i>

18:31.411 --> 18:33.544
<i> Adult mark: I had to do</i>
<i> something.</i>

18:33.679 --> 18:35.880
- [whispering loudly] ritchie!

18:36.015 --> 18:37.748
"do you have a reservation?"

18:39.018 --> 18:42.019
Audience: [indistinct murmurs]

18:42.021 --> 18:44.088
<i> Mark: Ritchie! Ritchie!</i>

18:44.090 --> 18:46.957
Ritchie!
"do you have a reservation?"

18:48.027 --> 18:51.829
Fox: I said, where shall we
seat him, hamar?

18:51.964 --> 18:54.031
[camera whirs,
audience murmurs]

18:57.703 --> 18:59.703
- This isn't how the play goes.
They're making an arse of it.

18:59.772 --> 19:01.973
- Shhh!
- Oh, shush yourself, ya hussy!

19:02.108 --> 19:03.507
- Will you shut it?!
- Oh, stuff it!

19:03.576 --> 19:05.242
- Shut your face!
- You're always in the middle.

19:05.278 --> 19:06.844
- Oh, please.

19:06.979 --> 19:08.779
<i> Adult mark: My best friend</i>
<i> needed help!</i>

19:08.848 --> 19:11.648
<i> I couldn't take it anymore.</i>

19:11.684 --> 19:14.451
<i> I had to act. Literally.</i>

19:14.521 --> 19:16.387
- [blows out his breath]
- not so fast!

19:16.522 --> 19:18.922
Stay the hell off my stage!
- Ritchie needs me!

19:19.058 --> 19:20.891
[struggling grunts]

19:20.960 --> 19:23.627
[mark grunts, light thump,
tray clatters]

19:23.696 --> 19:25.696
Parent: Where'd he come from?
- Oh my!

19:25.831 --> 19:27.765
[audience murmurs]
[camera whirs]

19:27.900 --> 19:30.201
<i>Adult mark: At least nobody was</i>
<i> looking at ritchie anymore.</i>

19:30.336 --> 19:32.736
- Hi.
[audience titters]

19:32.805 --> 19:35.005
- [sighs heavily]

19:35.041 --> 19:37.274
- Audience!
Welcome to the show!

19:37.343 --> 19:39.610
It is I, casca,
the roman centurion

19:39.746 --> 19:42.079
Who, who... Also picks up
a couple shifts

19:42.215 --> 19:43.748
Here at the restaurant.
[audience laughs]

19:43.750 --> 19:45.216
<i> Adult mark: I wanted to be</i>
<i> a comedian,</i>

19:45.351 --> 19:47.585
<i> So why not be a rodeo clown?</i>

19:47.654 --> 19:49.486
- What?!

19:49.522 --> 19:51.088
- Who wants bread?

19:51.224 --> 19:53.624
<i>Adult mark: Some would say I</i>
<i>was stalling to help my friend,</i>

19:53.626 --> 19:55.726
<i> Others might say</i>
<i> I was being a ham.</i>

19:55.861 --> 19:58.829
<i>Either way, this would be the</i>
<i> first last supper scene ever</i>

19:58.898 --> 20:00.965
With a happy ending.
- Get in here!

20:01.100 --> 20:03.234
- Oh... Nice place you got here.

20:03.369 --> 20:05.469
Ever think of doin' a...
A theme night?

20:05.505 --> 20:07.071
I guess toga parties would be...

20:07.206 --> 20:08.639
Too on the nose.
[everyone laughs]

20:08.675 --> 20:10.341
<i> Adult mark: These weren't</i>
<i> the lines</i>

20:10.476 --> 20:13.143
<i>I'd practiced with my father,</i>
<i> but he didn't seem to mind.</i>

20:13.213 --> 20:14.912
- Would it!
[audience laughs]

20:14.914 --> 20:16.313
- Get in.

20:16.349 --> 20:18.282
<i> Adult mark: And ritchie,</i>
<i> staying on theme,</i>

20:18.417 --> 20:20.050
<i> He rose again.</i>

20:20.086 --> 20:22.787
- Do you have a reservation?
- Nailed it!

20:22.922 --> 20:24.622
[audience laughs and claps]

20:24.691 --> 20:26.857
<i> Adult mark: Life is a lot</i>
<i> like a play.</i>

20:26.893 --> 20:30.261
<i> We all play different parts,</i>
<i> depending on who we're with.</i>

20:30.396 --> 20:33.064
<i> But there's no pretending</i>
<i> to be someone you're not</i>

20:33.066 --> 20:34.665
Around your family.
- Do you have a reservation?

20:34.701 --> 20:36.300
- [clapping] yeah, bravo!

20:36.435 --> 20:38.336
Bravo! Take a bow!

20:38.471 --> 20:40.337
<i> Adult mark: Dad turned out</i>
<i> to be my biggest fan.</i>

20:40.473 --> 20:42.006
- All right, couple o' notes.

20:42.141 --> 20:44.341
<i>Adult mark: And he was the only</i>
<i> audience I ever really wanted.</i>

20:44.377 --> 20:46.477
- If you're gonna take a bow,
you really wanna sweep

20:46.546 --> 20:48.846
The floor with your hand,
like that. Give it a try.

20:50.082 --> 20:52.883
A little lower.
Always get out there,

20:52.952 --> 20:55.019
And then just bask.

20:55.088 --> 20:57.688
[heartwarming music plays]

20:58.958 --> 21:00.958
<i> Adult mark: But the real actor</i>
<i> in the family</i>

21:01.027 --> 21:02.627
<i> Was the one acting</i>
<i> like he was tougher</i>

21:02.762 --> 21:05.029
<i> Than he really was.</i>

21:07.033 --> 21:08.366
- My beautiful girl.

21:10.236 --> 21:17.107
♪♪♪

21:17.143 --> 21:22.379
♪♪♪

